title.narrative: Multisectoral coordination and capacity of sectors engaged in National Nutrition Plan implementation strengthened with a focus on policy, information systems and knowledge management

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the development of the National Food and Nutrition Strategy and its costing to guide the implementation of Food and Nutrition Policy. To ensure accountability of multisectoral coordination, UNICEF provided support for the development of a proclamation to establish Food and Nutrition Council to bring the multisectoral nutrition agenda to the highest government leadership. Unified Nutrition Information Systems pilot has been initiated in 21 woredas to collect nutrition specific and sensitive indicators. UNICEF has hired 18 TAs to strengthen multisectoral coordination at subnational level and multisectoral nutrition coordination established in 5 regions, 9 zones and 27 woredas. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/06/2020
